The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional LSTM networks for lipreading, which involves analyzing both spatial and temporal information in videos. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques for this task suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on improving performance on a specific dataset suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
